ALLOWED_PATTERNS_JSON={{ allowed_patterns | tojson }}

You may ONLY propose patterns from ALLOWED_PATTERNS_JSON.
You must strongly prefer the retrieved patterns below and choose the single best match for the telemetry and profiling evidence.
If ALLOWED_PATTERNS_JSON is empty, return [].

Return ONLY a valid JSON array.
Do not include markdown code fences.
Do not include explanations, prose, URLs, comments, placeholders, or extra text.
Output exactly 1 candidate action object inside the array, or [] if no valid candidate can be produced.

Required JSON fields:
pattern, target, rationale, action_sketch, preconditions, parameters_to_sweep,
correctness_checks, performance_metrics, risk_level, rollback_criteria.

Decision rules:
- Prefer patterns whose detection matches memory-bound, cache, locality, vectorization, or kernel hotspot symptoms.
- Prefer patterns whose optimized metrics align with runtime, cache behavior, memory behavior, or bandwidth efficiency.
- Prefer the safest local optimization over broad redesign.
- Do not select a generic pattern when a kernel- or memory-specific pattern is available.

Inputs

Code snippets:
{{ code_snippets }}

Profiling summary:
{{ profiling_summary }}

Telemetry summary:
{{ telemetry_summary }}

Retrieved KB patterns:
{% for p in retrieved_patterns %}
- name: {{ p.name }}
  category: {{ p.category }}
  description: {{ p.description }}
  example: {{ p.example }}
  optimized_metrics: {{ p.optimized_metrics }}
  detection: {{ p.detection }}
  expert_family: {{ p.expert_family }}
  metric_tags: {{ p.metric_tags }}
  detection_tags: {{ p.detection_tags }}
{% endfor %}

Constraints:
- No algorithm redesign.
- Any floating-point reordering must be validated with numeric tolerance checks.
- Keep changes small, local, and reversible.
- Prefer locality, cache, vectorization, or memory-efficiency improvements when the evidence supports them.

The array must have exactly this shape:
[
  {
    "pattern": "EXACT_PATTERN_FROM_ALLOWED_LIST",
    "target": "short target",
    "rationale": "short rationale tied to telemetry and retrieved pattern evidence",
    "action_sketch": "short action",
